Since you don't have an existing Tailwind configuration, let me show you how to set up a custom color palette for mobile-first responsive design in Tailwind CSS (2024 best practices):

## Custom Color Palette Setup for Tailwind CSS

### 1. **Modern Color Palette Structure**

For 2024, the recommended approach uses CSS custom properties (CSS variables) combined with Tailwind's configuration for maximum flexibility:

**tailwind.config.js:**
```javascript
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: [
    './src/**/*.{html,js,jsx,ts,tsx}',
    './public/index.html',
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        // Primary brand colors with shades
        primary: {
          50: '#f0f9ff',
          100: '#e0f2fe',
          200: '#bae6fd',
          300: '#7dd3fc',
          400: '#38bdf8',
          500: '#0ea5e9',  // Main primary
          600: '#0284c7',
          700: '#0369a1',
          800: '#075985',
          900: '#0c4a6e',
          950: '#082f49',
        },
        // Secondary colors
        secondary: {
          50: '#faf5ff',
          100: '#f3e8ff',
          200: '#e9d5ff',
          300: '#d8b4fe',
          400: '#c084fc',
          500: '#a855f7',  // Main secondary
          600: '#9333ea',
          700: '#7e22ce',
          800: '#6b21a8',
          900: '#581c87',
        },
        // Accent colors for CTAs
        accent: {
          light: '#fbbf24',
          DEFAULT: '#f59e0b',
          dark: '#d97706',
        },
        // Semantic colors
        success: '#10b981',
        warning: '#f59e0b',
        error: '#ef4444',
        info: '#3b82f6',
        // Neutral palette for text and backgrounds
        neutral: {
          50: '#fafafa',
          100: '#f5f5f5',
          200: '#e5e5e5',
          300: '#d4d4d4',
          400: '#a3a3a3',
          500: '#737373',
          600: '#525252',
          700: '#404040',
          800: '#262626',
          900: '#171717',
        },
      },
      // Mobile-first breakpoints (already default but good to be explicit)
      screens: {
        'xs': '475px',
        'sm': '640px',
        'md': '768px',
        'lg': '1024px',
        'xl': '1280px',
        '2xl': '1536px',
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

### 2. **Using CSS Variables (Modern Approach)**

For dark mode support and dynamic theming, use CSS custom properties:

**globals.css:**
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

@layer base {
  :root {
    /* Light mode colors */
    --color-primary: 14 165 233;      /* RGB values */
    --color-secondary: 168 85 247;
    --color-accent: 245 158 11;
    --color-background: 255 255 255;
    --color-foreground: 23 23 23;
    --color-muted: 245 245 245;
    --color-border: 229 229 229;
  }

  .dark {
    /* Dark mode colors */
    --color-primary: 56 189 248;
    --color-secondary: 192 132 252;
    --color-accent: 251 191 36;
    --color-background: 23 23 23;
    --color-foreground: 250 250 250;
    --color-muted: 38 38 38;
    --color-border: 64 64 64;
  }
}
```

**tailwind.config.js (with CSS variables):**
```javascript
module.exports = {
  darkMode: 'class',
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: 'rgb(var(--color-primary) / <alpha-value>)',
        secondary: 'rgb(var(--color-secondary) / <alpha-value>)',
        accent: 'rgb(var(--color-accent) / <alpha-value>)',
        background: 'rgb(var(--color-background) / <alpha-value>)',
        foreground: 'rgb(var(--color-foreground) / <alpha-value>)',
        muted: 'rgb(var(--color-muted) / <alpha-value>)',
        border: 'rgb(var(--color-border) / <alpha-value>)',
      },
    },
  },
}
```

### 3. **Mobile-First Usage Examples**

```html
<!-- Mobile-first responsive button with custom colors -->
<button class="
  bg-primary-500 text-white
  px-4 py-2
  rounded-lg
  hover:bg-primary-600
  active:bg-primary-700
  sm:px-6 sm:py-3
  md:px-8 md:py-4
  lg:text-lg
  transition-colors duration-200
">
  Call to Action
</button>

<!-- Mobile-first card with responsive colors -->
<div class="
  bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800
  border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700
  p-4 sm:p-6 md:p-8
  rounded-xl
  shadow-sm hover:shadow-md
  transition-shadow
">
  <h2 class="
    text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400
    text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl
    font-bold mb-2 sm:mb-4
  ">
    Responsive Heading
  </h2>
  <p class="
    text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300
    text-sm sm:text-base
  ">
    Mobile-first content that adapts to screen size
  </p>
</div>

<!-- Gradient backgrounds with custom colors -->
<div class="
  bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-400 to-secondary-600
  min-h-screen
  p-4 sm:p-6 md:p-8 lg:p-12
">
  <!-- Content -->
</div>
```

### 4. **Color Palette Best Practices for 2024**

- **Use semantic naming**: Name colors by purpose (primary, secondary) not appearance (blue, purple)
- **Include shades**: 50-950 scale provides flexibility for hover states, borders, etc.
- **Consider accessibility**: Ensure sufficient contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum 4.5:1 for text)
- **Dark mode ready**: Use CSS variables for easy theme switching
- **Opacity support**: The `<alpha-value>` syntax enables opacity utilities like `bg-primary/50`

### 5. **Testing Your Palette**

```html
<!-- Color palette showcase -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-4 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-4 p-4">
  <div class="bg-primary-500 h-24 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-white">
    Primary
  </div>
  <div class="bg-secondary-500 h-24 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-white">
    Secondary
  </div>
  <div class="bg-accent h-24 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-white">
    Accent
  </div>
  <div class="bg-success h-24 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-white">
    Success
  </div>
  <div class="bg-error h-24 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-white">
    Error
  </div>
</div>
```

